            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "While I assume that `__ne__ = __eq__` is just a meaningless example, I think it makes sense to allow at least assignments of other dunder methods of the same class â€“ as long as both signatures are the same. That would allow aliasing slot methods.\r\n\r\nThat being said, it would be nice to see an actual use case for this first.",
